Umbra Heartspire is a failed judicial-religious archive beneath Midgaard.
It began as an extension of Midgaard's record culture, absorbed Kiess's funerary rites after Evermeet's fall, and was consumed by a shadow creed.

Chartered during Midgaard's containment era to hold sensitive materials: sealed witness statements, disputed noble titles, war-crime depositions, ritual contracts.
First stewards were archivist-clerks and oath-wardens seconded from city offices.

After Evermeet's fall, Kiess displaced houses brought funerary law and mirror-testimony customs.
Hearings became processions. Clerks became cantors. Archive halls gained chapel functions.

The Iron Wake reforms militarized the institution. Doctrine: preserve the institution first, records second, people if possible.
A later faction built orreries and omen laboratories in the upper spire, making procedure predictive. Appeal rights collapsed because outcomes were framed as cosmically ratified.

Abbot Noctivar united remaining orders under the Ebon Pulse creed: all testimony decays, only curated shadow keeps civilization intact.
Under this creed, falsification is reframed as mercy.
The Heartspire no longer stores truth. It manufactures survivable narratives.
